    "actions": [
      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Scythe Slash (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Bladewing swoops down at a target, using its razor-sharp wings to slash. It makes a melee attack, dealing D6 Slashing damage on a hit. If the target is wearing no Armor, they are now Bleeding (1).</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 4,
        "name": "Shadow Dive",
        "description": "<div><p>The Bladewing disappears into the shadows, increasing its Combat Skill for any defensive check by 10 until its next turn.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 5,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Shrieking Assault",
        "description": "<div><p>The Bladewing screeches loudly, unsettling and distracting all creatures. Affected creatures must succeed on a Resolve check or have Disadvantage on their next attack roll. Additionally, the Bladewing can then make a melee attack as a Free Action against one of the affected creatures, dealing D6 Slashing damage on a hit.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>Bladewings are small, bat-like creatures with wings resembling sharp, scythe-like blades that glint with a metallic shine. Each Bladewing is covered in sleek, obsidian-black fur, allowing them to blend seamlessly into the shadows as they take flight with uncanny grace and speed. These nightmarish creatures unleash a haunting screech as they descend upon their prey, their razor-sharp wings capable of slicing through flesh with ease.</p></div>",
